47static constexpr LiftoffRegList kByteRegs =
48 LiftoffRegList::FromBits<RegList{eax, ecx, edx}.bits()>();

50inline void Load(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst, Register base,
51 int32_t offset, ValueKind kind) {
52 Operand src(base, offset);
53 switch (kind) {
54 case kI16:
55 assm->mov_w(dst.gp(), src);
56 break;
57 case kI32:
58 case kRefNull:
59 case kRef:
60 case kRtt:
61 assm->mov(dst.gp(), src);
62 break;
63 case kI64:
64 assm->mov(dst.low_gp(), src);
65 assm->mov(dst.high_gp(), Operand(base, offset + 4));
66 break;
67 case kF32:
68 assm->movss(dst.fp(), src);
69 break;
70 case kF64:
71 assm->movsd(dst.fp(), src);
72 break;
73 case kS128:
74 assm->movdqu(dst.fp(), src);
75 break;
76 case kVoid:
77 case kTop:
78 case kBottom:
79 case kI8:
80 case kF16:
81 UNREACHABLE();
82 }
83}
84
85inline void Store(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register base, int32_t offset,
86 LiftoffRegister src, ValueKind kind) {
87 Operand dst(base, offset);
88 switch (kind) {
89 case kI16:
90 assm->mov_w(dst, src.gp());
91 break;
92 case kI32:
93 case kRefNull:
94 case kRef:
95 case kRtt:
96 assm->mov(dst, src.gp());
97 break;
98 case kI64:
99 assm->mov(dst, src.low_gp());
100 assm->mov(Operand(base, offset + 4), src.high_gp());
101 break;
102 case kF32:
103 assm->movss(dst, src.fp());
104 break;
105 case kF64:
106 assm->movsd(dst, src.fp());
107 break;
108 case kS128:
109 assm->movdqu(dst, src.fp());
110 break;
111 case kVoid:
112 case kTop:
113 case kBottom:
114 case kI8:
115 case kF16:
116 UNREACHABLE();
117 }
118}

120inline void push(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister reg, ValueKind kind,
121 int padding = 0) {
122 switch (kind) {
123 case kI32:
124 case kRef:
125 case kRefNull:
126 case kRtt:
127 assm->AllocateStackSpace(padding);
128 assm->push(reg.gp());
129 break;
130 case kI64:
131 assm->AllocateStackSpace(padding);
132 assm->push(reg.high_gp());
133 assm->push(reg.low_gp());
134 break;
135 case kF32:
136 assm->AllocateStackSpace(sizeof(float) + padding);
137 assm->movss(Operand(esp, 0), reg.fp());
138 break;
139 case kF64:
140 assm->AllocateStackSpace(sizeof(double) + padding);
141 assm->movsd(Operand(esp, 0), reg.fp());
142 break;
143 case kS128:
144 assm->AllocateStackSpace(sizeof(double) * 2 + padding);
145 assm->movdqu(Operand(esp, 0), reg.fp());
146 break;
147 case kVoid:
148 case kTop:
149 case kBottom:
150 case kI8:
151 case kI16:
152 case kF16:
153 UNREACHABLE();
154 }
155}

157inline void SignExtendI32ToI64(Assembler* assm, LiftoffRegister reg) {
158 assm->mov(reg.high_gp(), reg.low_gp());
159 assm->sar(reg.high_gp(), 31);
160}

162// Get a temporary byte register, using {candidate} if possible.
163// Might spill, but always keeps status flags intact.
164inline Register GetTmpByteRegister(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register candidate) {
165 if (candidate.is_byte_register()) return candidate;
166 // {GetUnusedRegister()} may insert move instructions to spill registers to
167 // the stack. This is OK because {mov} does not change the status flags.
168 return assm->GetUnusedRegister(liftoff::kByteRegs).gp();
169}
170
171inline void MoveStackValue(LiftoffAssembler* assm, const Operand& src,
172 const Operand& dst) {
173 if (assm->cache_state()->has_unused_register(kGpReg)) {
174 Register tmp = assm->cache_state()->unused_register(kGpReg).gp();
175 assm->mov(tmp, src);
176 assm->mov(dst, tmp);
177 } else {
178 // No free register, move via the stack.
179 assm->push(src);
180 assm->pop(dst);
181 }
182}

184class CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters {
185 public:
186 explicit CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
187 LiftoffRegList pinned = {})
188 : assm_(assm), pinned_(pinned) {}
189
190 ~CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters() {
191 for (Register reg : must_pop_) {
192 assm_->pop(reg);
193 }
194 }
195
196 Register Acquire() {
197 if (assm_->cache_state()->has_unused_register(kGpReg, pinned_)) {
198 return pinned_.set(
199 assm_->cache_state()->unused_register(kGpReg, pinned_).gp());
200 }
201
202 RegList available =
203 kLiftoffAssemblerGpCacheRegs - pinned_.GetGpList() - must_pop_;
204 DCHECK(!available.is_empty());
205 // Use {last()} here so we can just iterate forwards in the destructor.
206 Register reg = available.last();
207 assm_->push(reg);
208 must_pop_.set(reg);
209 return reg;
210 }
211
212 private:
213 LiftoffAssembler* const assm_;
214 LiftoffRegList pinned_;
215 RegList must_pop_;
216};

224int LiftoffAssembler::PrepareStackFrame() {
225 int offset = pc_offset();
226 // Next we reserve the memory for the whole stack frame. We do not know yet
227 // how big the stack frame will be so we just emit a placeholder instruction.
228 // PatchPrepareStackFrame will patch this in order to increase the stack
229 // appropriately.
230 sub_sp_32(0);
231 DCHECK_EQ(liftoff::kSubSpSize, pc_offset() - offset);
232 return offset;
233}

235void LiftoffAssembler::CallFrameSetupStub(int declared_function_index) {
236// The standard library used by gcc tryjobs does not consider `std::find` to be
237// `constexpr`, so wrap it in a `#ifdef __clang__` block.
238#ifdef __clang__
239 static_assert(std::find(std::begin(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
240 std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
241 kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg) ==
242 std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters));
243#endif
244
245 LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister(kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg),
246 WasmValue(declared_function_index));
247 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmLiftoffFrameSetup);
248}

250void LiftoffAssembler::PrepareTailCall(int num_callee_stack_params,
251 int stack_param_delta) {
252 // Push the return address and frame pointer to complete the stack frame.
253 push(Operand(ebp, 4));
254 push(Operand(ebp, 0));
255
256 // Shift the whole frame upwards.
257 Register scratch = eax;
258 push(scratch);
259 const int slot_count = num_callee_stack_params + 2;
260 for (int i = slot_count; i > 0; --i) {
261 mov(scratch, Operand(esp, i * 4));
262 mov(Operand(ebp, (i - stack_param_delta - 1) * 4), scratch);
263 }
264 pop(scratch);
265
266 // Set the new stack and frame pointers.
267 lea(esp, Operand(ebp, -stack_param_delta * 4));
268 pop(ebp);
269}

273void LiftoffAssembler::PatchPrepareStackFrame(
274 int offset, SafepointTableBuilder* safepoint_table_builder,
275 bool feedback_vector_slot, size_t stack_param_slots) {
276 // The frame_size includes the frame marker and the instance slot. Both are
277 // pushed as part of frame construction, so we don't need to allocate memory
278 // for them anymore.
279 int frame_size = GetTotalFrameSize() - 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
280 // The frame setup builtin also pushes the feedback vector.
281 if (feedback_vector_slot) {
282 frame_size -= kSystemPointerSize;
283 }
284 DCHECK_EQ(0, frame_size % kSystemPointerSize);
285
286 // We can't run out of space when patching, just pass anything big enough to
287 // not cause the assembler to try to grow the buffer.
288 constexpr int kAvailableSpace = 64;
289 Assembler patching_assembler(
290 AssemblerOptions{},
291 ExternalAssemblerBuffer(buffer_start_ + offset, kAvailableSpace));
292
293 if (V8_LIKELY(frame_size < 4 * KB)) {
294 // This is the standard case for small frames: just subtract from SP and be
295 // done with it.
296 patching_assembler.sub_sp_32(frame_size);
297 DCHECK_EQ(liftoff::kSubSpSize, patching_assembler.pc_offset());
298 return;
299 }
300
301 // The frame size is bigger than 4KB, so we might overflow the available stack
302 // space if we first allocate the frame and then do the stack check (we will
303 // need some remaining stack space for throwing the exception). That's why we
304 // check the available stack space before we allocate the frame. To do this we
305 // replace the {__ sub(sp, framesize)} with a jump to OOL code that does this
306 // "extended stack check".
307 //
308 // The OOL code can simply be generated here with the normal assembler,
309 // because all other code generation, including OOL code, has already finished
310 // when {PatchPrepareStackFrame} is called. The function prologue then jumps
311 // to the current {pc_offset()} to execute the OOL code for allocating the
312 // large frame.
313
314 // Emit the unconditional branch in the function prologue (from {offset} to
315 // {pc_offset()}).
316 patching_assembler.jmp_rel(pc_offset() - offset);
317 DCHECK_GE(liftoff::kSubSpSize, patching_assembler.pc_offset());
318 patching_assembler.Nop(liftoff::kSubSpSize - patching_assembler.pc_offset());
319
320 // If the frame is bigger than the stack, we throw the stack overflow
321 // exception unconditionally. Thereby we can avoid the integer overflow
322 // check in the condition code.
323 RecordComment("OOL: stack check for large frame");
324 Label continuation;
325 if (frame_size < v8_flags.stack_size * 1024) {
326 // We do not have a scratch register, so pick any and push it first.
327 Register stack_limit = eax;
328 push(stack_limit);
329 mov(stack_limit, esp);
330 sub(stack_limit, Immediate(frame_size));
331 CompareStackLimit(stack_limit, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
332 pop(stack_limit);
333 j(above_equal, &continuation, Label::kNear);
334 }
335
336 if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
337 LiftoffRegList regs_to_save;
338 regs_to_save.set(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister());
339 regs_to_save.set(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister());
340 for (auto reg : kGpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
341 for (auto reg : kFpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
342 PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
343 mov(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister(),
344 Immediate(frame_size));
345 mov(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister(), ebp);
346 add(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister(),
347 Immediate(static_cast<int32_t>(
348 stack_param_slots * kStackSlotSize +
349 CommonFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp)));
350 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmHandleStackOverflow);
351 PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
352 } else {
353 wasm_call(static_cast<intptr_t>(Builtin::kWasmStackOverflow),
354 RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
355 // The call will not return; just define an empty safepoint.
356 safepoint_table_builder->DefineSafepoint(this);
357 AssertUnreachable(AbortReason::kUnexpectedReturnFromWasmTrap);
358 }
359
360 bind(&continuation);
361
362 // Now allocate the stack space. Note that this might do more than just
363 // decrementing the SP; consult {MacroAssembler::AllocateStackSpace}.
364 AllocateStackSpace(frame_size);
365
366 // Jump back to the start of the function, from {pc_offset()} to
367 // right after the reserved space for the {__ sub(sp, sp, framesize)} (which
368 // is a branch now).
369 int func_start_offset = offset + liftoff::kSubSpSize;
370 jmp_rel(func_start_offset - pc_offset());
371}

390void LiftoffAssembler::CheckTierUp(int declared_func_index, int budget_used,
391 Label* ool_label,
392 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
393 {
394 liftoff::CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters temps{this};
395 Register budget_array = temps.Acquire();
396
397 Register instance_data = cache_state_.cached_instance_data;
398 if (instance_data == no_reg) {
399 instance_data = budget_array; // Reuse the temp register.
400 LoadInstanceDataFromFrame(instance_data);
401 }
402
403 constexpr int kArrayOffset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
404 WasmTrustedInstanceData::kTieringBudgetArrayOffset);
405 mov(budget_array, Operand{instance_data, kArrayOffset});
406
407 int array_offset = kInt32Size * declared_func_index;
408 sub(Operand{budget_array, array_offset}, Immediate(budget_used));
409 }
410 j(negative, ool_label);
411}

413Register LiftoffAssembler::LoadOldFramePointer() {
414 if (!v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
415 return ebp;
416 }
417 Label done, call_runtime;
418 cmp(MemOperand(ebp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset),
419 Immediate(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
420 j(equal, &call_runtime);
421 LiftoffRegister old_fp = GetUnusedRegister(RegClass::kGpReg, {});
422 mov(old_fp.gp(), ebp);
423 jmp(&done);
424
425 bind(&call_runtime);
426 LiftoffRegList regs_to_save = cache_state()->used_registers;
427 PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
428 PrepareCallCFunction(1, eax);
429 MacroAssembler::Move(Operand(esp, 0 * kSystemPointerSize),
430 Immediate(ExternalReference::isolate_address()));
431 CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_load_old_fp(), 1);
432 if (old_fp.gp() != kReturnRegister0) {
433 mov(old_fp.gp(), kReturnRegister0);
434 }
435 PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
436
437 bind(&done);
438 return old_fp.gp();
439}

441void LiftoffAssembler::CheckStackShrink() {
442 LiftoffRegList regs_to_save;
443 for (auto reg : kGpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
444 for (auto reg : kFpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
445 cmp(MemOperand(ebp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset),
446 Immediate(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
447 Label done;
448 j(not_equal, &done);
449 PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
450 PrepareCallCFunction(1, kReturnRegister0);
451 MacroAssembler::Move(Operand(esp, 0 * kSystemPointerSize),
452 Immediate(ExternalReference::isolate_address()));
453 CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_shrink_stack(), 1);
454 // Restore old ebp. We don't need to restore old esp explicitly, because
455 // it will be restored from ebp in LeaveFrame before return.
456 mov(ebp, kReturnRegister0);
457 PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
458 bind(&done);
459}

461void LiftoffAssembler::LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister reg, WasmValue value) {
462 switch (value.type().kind()) {
463 case kI32:
464 MacroAssembler::Move(reg.gp(), Immediate(value.to_i32()));
465 break;
466 case kI64: {
467 int32_t low_word = value.to_i64();
468 int32_t high_word = value.to_i64() >> 32;
469 MacroAssembler::Move(reg.low_gp(), Immediate(low_word));
470 MacroAssembler::Move(reg.high_gp(), Immediate(high_word));
471 break;
472 }
473 case kF32:
474 MacroAssembler::Move(reg.fp(), value.to_f32_boxed().get_bits());
475 break;
476 case kF64:
477 MacroAssembler::Move(reg.fp(), value.to_f64_boxed().get_bits());
478 break;
479 default:
480 UNREACHABLE();
481 }
482}

547void LiftoffAssembler::StoreTaggedPointer(Register dst_addr,
548 Register offset_reg,
549 int32_t offset_imm, Register src,
550 LiftoffRegList pinned,
551 uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
552 SkipWriteBarrier skip_write_barrier) {
553 DCHECK_GE(offset_imm, 0);
554 DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
555 static_assert(kTaggedSize == kInt32Size);
556 Operand dst_op = liftoff::MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
557
558 if (protected_store_pc) *protected_store_pc = pc_offset();
559
560 mov(dst_op, src);
561
562 if (skip_write_barrier || v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) return;
563
564 liftoff::CacheStatePreservingTempRegisters temps{this, pinned};
565 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
566
567 Label exit;
568 CheckPageFlag(dst_addr, scratch,
569 MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask, zero, &exit,
570 Label::kNear);
571 JumpIfSmi(src, &exit, Label::kNear);
572 CheckPageFlag(src, scratch, MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask,
573 zero, &exit, Label::kNear);
574 lea(scratch, dst_op);
575 CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(dst_addr, scratch, SaveFPRegsMode::kSave,
576 StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
577 bind(&exit);
578}

580void LiftoffAssembler::Load(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
581 Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
582 LoadType type, uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
583 bool /* is_load_mem */, bool /* i64_offset */,
584 bool needs_shift) {
585 // Offsets >=2GB are statically OOB on 32-bit systems.
586 DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
587 DCHECK_EQ(type.value_type() == kWasmI64, dst.is_gp_pair());
588 ScaleFactor scale_factor =
589 !needs_shift ? times_1 : static_cast<ScaleFactor>(type.size_log_2());
590 Operand src_op = offset_reg == no_reg ? Operand(src_addr, offset_imm)
591 : Operand(src_addr, offset_reg,
592 scale_factor, offset_imm);
593 if (protected_load_pc) *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
594
595 switch (type.value()) {
596 case LoadType::kI32Load8U:
597 movzx_b(dst.gp(), src_op);
598 break;
599 case LoadType::kI32Load8S:
600 movsx_b(dst.gp(), src_op);
601 break;
602 case LoadType::kI64Load8U:
603 movzx_b(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
604 xor_(dst.high_gp(), dst.high_gp());
605 break;
606 case LoadType::kI64Load8S:
607 movsx_b(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
608 liftoff::SignExtendI32ToI64(this, dst);
609 break;
610 case LoadType::kI32Load16U:
611 movzx_w(dst.gp(), src_op);
612 break;
613 case LoadType::kI32Load16S:
614 movsx_w(dst.gp(), src_op);
615 break;
616 case LoadType::kI64Load16U:
617 movzx_w(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
618 xor_(dst.high_gp(), dst.high_gp());
619 break;
620 case LoadType::kI64Load16S:
621 movsx_w(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
622 liftoff::SignExtendI32ToI64(this, dst);
623 break;
624 case LoadType::kI32Load:
625 mov(dst.gp(), src_op);
626 break;
627 case LoadType::kI64Load32U:
628 mov(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
629 xor_(dst.high_gp(), dst.high_gp());
630 break;
631 case LoadType::kI64Load32S:
632 mov(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
633 liftoff::SignExtendI32ToI64(this, dst);
634 break;
635 case LoadType::kI64Load: {
636 // Compute the operand for the load of the upper half.
637 Operand upper_src_op =
638 liftoff::MemOperand(src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm + 4);
639 // The high word has to be mov'ed first, such that this is the protected
640 // instruction. The mov of the low word cannot segfault.
641 mov(dst.high_gp(), upper_src_op);
642 mov(dst.low_gp(), src_op);
643 break;
644 }
645 case LoadType::kF32Load:
646 movss(dst.fp(), src_op);
647 break;
648 case LoadType::kF64Load:
649 movsd(dst.fp(), src_op);
650 break;
651 case LoadType::kS128Load:
652 movdqu(dst.fp(), src_op);
653 break;
654 case LoadType::kF32LoadF16:
655 UNIMPLEMENTED();
656 break;
657 }
658}
659
660void LiftoffAssembler::Store(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
661 uint32_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
662 StoreType type, LiftoffRegList pinned,
663 uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
664 bool /* is_store_mem */, bool /* i64_offset */) {
665 DCHECK_EQ(type.value_type() == kWasmI64, src.is_gp_pair());
666 // Offsets >=2GB are statically OOB on 32-bit systems.
667 DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
668 Operand dst_op = liftoff::MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
669 if (protected_store_pc) *protected_store_pc = pc_offset();
670
671 switch (type.value()) {
672 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
673 src = src.low();
674 [[fallthrough]];
675 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
676 // Only the lower 4 registers can be addressed as 8-bit registers.
677 if (src.gp().is_byte_register()) {
678 mov_b(dst_op, src.gp());
679 } else {
680 // We know that {src} is not a byte register, so the only pinned byte
681 // registers (beside the outer {pinned}) are {dst_addr} and potentially
682 // {offset_reg}.
683 LiftoffRegList pinned_byte = pinned | LiftoffRegList{dst_addr};
684 if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned_byte.set(offset_reg);
685 LiftoffRegList candidates = liftoff::kByteRegs.MaskOut(pinned_byte);
686 if (cache_state_.has_unused_register(candidates)) {
687 Register byte_src = cache_state_.unused_register(candidates).gp();
688 mov(byte_src, src.gp());
689 mov_b(dst_op, byte_src);
690 } else {
691 // We have no available byte register. We will temporarily push the
692 // root register to use it as a scratch register.
693 static_assert(kRootRegister == ebx);
694 Register byte_src = kRootRegister;
695 Push(byte_src);
696 mov(byte_src, src.gp());
697 mov_b(dst_op, byte_src);
698 Pop(byte_src);
699 }
700 }
701 break;
702 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
703 src = src.low();
704 [[fallthrough]];
705 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
706 mov_w(dst_op, src.gp());
707 break;
708 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
709 src = src.low();
710 [[fallthrough]];
711 case StoreType::kI32Store:
712 mov(dst_op, src.gp());
713 break;
714 case StoreType::kI64Store: {
715 // Compute the operand for the store of the upper half.
716 Operand upper_dst_op =
717 liftoff::MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm + 4);
718 // The high word has to be mov'ed first, such that this is the protected
719 // instruction. The mov of the low word cannot segfault.
720 mov(upper_dst_op, src.high_gp());
721 mov(dst_op, src.low_gp());
722 break;
723 }
724 case StoreType::kF32Store:
725 movss(dst_op, src.fp());
726 break;
727 case StoreType::kF64Store:
728 movsd(dst_op, src.fp());
729 break;
730 case StoreType::kS128Store:
731 Movdqu(dst_op, src.fp());
732 break;
733 case StoreType::kF32StoreF16:
734 UNIMPLEMENTED();
735 break;
736 }
737}
738
739void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicLoad(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
740 Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
741 LoadType type, LiftoffRegList /* pinned */,
742 bool /* i64_offset */) {
743 if (type.value() != LoadType::kI64Load) {
744 Load(dst, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, type, nullptr, true);
745 return;
746 }
747
748 DCHECK_EQ(type.value_type() == kWasmI64, dst.is_gp_pair());
749 DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
750 Operand src_op = liftoff::MemOperand(src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
751
752 movsd(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, src_op);
753 Pextrd(dst.low().gp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, 0);
754 Pextrd(dst.high().gp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, 1);
755}
756
757void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicStore(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
758 uint32_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
759 StoreType type, LiftoffRegList pinned,
760 bool /* i64_offset */) {
761 DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
762 Operand dst_op = liftoff::MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
763
764 // i64 store uses a totally different approach, hence implement it separately.
765 if (type.value() == StoreType::kI64Store) {
766 auto scratch2 = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, pinned).fp();
767 movd(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, src.low().gp());
768 movd(scratch2, src.high().gp());
769 Punpckldq(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, scratch2);
770 movsd(dst_op, liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
771 // This lock+or is needed to achieve sequential consistency.
772 lock();
773 or_(Operand(esp, 0), Immediate(0));
774 return;
775 }
776
777 // Other i64 stores actually only use the low word.
778 if (src.is_pair()) src = src.low();
779 Register src_gp = src.gp();
780
781 bool is_byte_store = type.size() == 1;
782 LiftoffRegList src_candidates =
783 is_byte_store ? liftoff::kByteRegs : kGpCacheRegList;
784 pinned = pinned | LiftoffRegList{dst_addr, src};
785 if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
786
787 // Ensure that {src} is a valid and otherwise unused register.
788 if (!src_candidates.has(src) || cache_state_.is_used(src)) {
789 // If there are no unused candidate registers, but {src} is a candidate,
790 // then spill other uses of {src}. Otherwise spill any candidate register
791 // and use that.
792 LiftoffRegList unpinned_candidates = src_candidates.MaskOut(pinned);
793 if (!cache_state_.has_unused_register(unpinned_candidates) &&
794 src_candidates.has(src)) {
795 SpillRegister(src);
796 } else {
797 Register safe_src = GetUnusedRegister(unpinned_candidates).gp();
798 mov(safe_src, src_gp);
799 src_gp = safe_src;
800 }
801 }
802
803 switch (type.value()) {
804 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
805 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
806 xchg_b(src_gp, dst_op);
807 return;
808 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
809 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
810 xchg_w(src_gp, dst_op);
811 return;
812 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
813 case StoreType::kI32Store:
814 xchg(src_gp, dst_op);
815 return;
816 default:
817 UNREACHABLE();
818 }
819}

821namespace liftoff {
822#define __ lasm->
823
824enum Binop { kAdd, kSub, kAnd, kOr, kXor, kExchange };
825
826inline void AtomicAddOrSubOrExchange32(LiftoffAssembler* lasm, Binop binop,
827 Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
828 uint32_t offset_imm,
829 LiftoffRegister value,
830 LiftoffRegister result, StoreType type) {
831 DCHECK_EQ(value, result);
832 DCHECK(!__ cache_state()->is_used(result));
833 bool is_64_bit_op = type.value_type() == kWasmI64;
834
835 Register value_reg = is_64_bit_op ? value.low_gp() : value.gp();
836 Register result_reg = is_64_bit_op ? result.low_gp() : result.gp();
837
838 bool is_byte_store = type.size() == 1;
839 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, value_reg};
840 if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
841
842 // Ensure that {value_reg} is a valid register.
843 if (is_byte_store && !liftoff::kByteRegs.has(value_reg)) {
844 Register safe_value_reg =
845 __ GetUnusedRegister(liftoff::kByteRegs.MaskOut(pinned)).gp();
846 __ mov(safe_value_reg, value_reg);
847 value_reg = safe_value_reg;
848 }
849
850 Operand dst_op = liftoff::MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
851 if (binop == kSub) {
852 __ neg(value_reg);
853 }
854 if (binop != kExchange) {
855 __ lock();
856 }
857 switch (type.value()) {
858 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
859 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
860 if (binop == kExchange) {
861 __ xchg_b(value_reg, dst_op);
862 } else {
863 __ xadd_b(dst_op, value_reg);
864 }
865 __ movzx_b(result_reg, value_reg);
866 break;
867 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
868 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
869 if (binop == kExchange) {
870 __ xchg_w(value_reg, dst_op);
871 } else {
872 __ xadd_w(dst_op, value_reg);
873 }
874 __ movzx_w(result_reg, value_reg);
875 break;
876 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
877 case StoreType::kI32Store:
878 if (binop == kExchange) {
879 __ xchg(value_reg, dst_op);
880 } else {
881 __ xadd(dst_op, value_reg);
882 }
883 if (value_reg != result_reg) {
884 __ mov(result_reg, value_reg);
885 }
886 break;
887 default:
888 UNREACHABLE();
889 }
890 if (is_64_bit_op) {
891 __ xor_(result.high_gp(), result.high_gp());
892 }
893}
894
895inline void AtomicBinop32(LiftoffAssembler* lasm, Binop op, Register dst_addr,
896 Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
897 LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister result,
898 StoreType type) {
899 DCHECK_EQ(value, result);
900 DCHECK(!__ cache_state()->is_used(result));
901 bool is_64_bit_op = type.value_type() == kWasmI64;
902
903 Register value_reg = is_64_bit_op ? value.low_gp() : value.gp();
904 Register result_reg = is_64_bit_op ? result.low_gp() : result.gp();
905
906 // The cmpxchg instruction uses eax to store the old value of the
907 // compare-exchange primitive. Therefore we have to spill the register and
908 // move any use to another register.
909 {
910 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, value_reg};
911 if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
912 __ ClearRegister(eax, {&dst_addr, &offset_reg, &value_reg}, pinned);
913 }
914
915 bool is_byte_store = type.size() == 1;
916 Register scratch = no_reg;
917 if (is_byte_store) {
918 // The scratch register has to be a byte register. As we are already tight
919 // on registers, we just use the root register here.
920 static_assert(!kLiftoffAssemblerGpCacheRegs.has(kRootRegister),
921 "root register is not Liftoff cache register");
922 DCHECK(kRootRegister.is_byte_register());
923 __ push(kRootRegister);
924 scratch = kRootRegister;
925 } else {
926 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, value_reg, eax};
927 if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
928 scratch = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
929 }
930
931 Operand dst_op = liftoff::MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
932
933 switch (type.value()) {
934 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
935 case StoreType::kI64Store8: {
936 __ xor_(eax, eax);
937 __ mov_b(eax, dst_op);
938 break;
939 }
940 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
941 case StoreType::kI64Store16: {
942 __ xor_(eax, eax);
943 __ mov_w(eax, dst_op);
944 break;
945 }
946 case StoreType::kI32Store:
947 case StoreType::kI64Store32: {
948 __ mov(eax, dst_op);
949 break;
950 }
951 default:
952 UNREACHABLE();
953 }
954
955 Label binop;
956 __ bind(&binop);
957 __ mov(scratch, eax);
958
959 switch (op) {
960 case kAnd: {
961 __ and_(scratch, value_reg);
962 break;
963 }
964 case kOr: {
965 __ or_(scratch, value_reg);
966 break;
967 }
968 case kXor: {
969 __ xor_(scratch, value_reg);
970 break;
971 }
972 default:
973 UNREACHABLE();
974 }
975
976 __ lock();
977
978 switch (type.value()) {
979 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
980 case StoreType::kI64Store8: {
981 __ cmpxchg_b(dst_op, scratch);
982 break;
983 }
984 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
985 case StoreType::kI64Store16: {
986 __ cmpxchg_w(dst_op, scratch);
987 break;
988 }
989 case StoreType::kI32Store:
990 case StoreType::kI64Store32: {
991 __ cmpxchg(dst_op, scratch);
992 break;
993 }
994 default:
995 UNREACHABLE();
996 }
997 __ j(not_equal, &binop);
998
999 if (is_byte_store) {
1000 __ pop(kRootRegister);
1001 }
1002 if (result_reg != eax) {
1003 __ mov(result_reg, eax);
1004 }
1005 if (is_64_bit_op) {
1006 __ xor_(result.high_gp(), result.high_gp());
1007 }
1008}
1009
1010inline void AtomicBinop64(LiftoffAssembler* lasm, Binop op, Register dst_addr,
1011 Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
1012 LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister result) {
1013 // We need {ebx} here, which is the root register. As the root register it
1014 // needs special treatment. As we use {ebx} directly in the code below, we
1015 // have to make sure here that the root register is actually {ebx}.
1016 static_assert(kRootRegister == ebx,
1017 "The following code assumes that kRootRegister == ebx");
1018 __ push(ebx);
1019
1020 // Store the value on the stack, so that we can use it for retries.
1021 __ AllocateStackSpace(8);
1022 Operand value_op_hi = Operand(esp, 0);
1023 Operand value_op_lo = Operand(esp, 4);
1024 __ mov(value_op_lo, value.low_gp());
1025 __ mov(value_op_hi, value.high_gp());
1026
1027 // We want to use the compare-exchange instruction here. It uses registers
1028 // as follows: old-value = EDX:EAX; new-value = ECX:EBX.
1029 Register old_hi = edx;
1030 Register old_lo = eax;
1031 Register new_hi = ecx;
1032 Register new_lo = ebx;
1033 // Base and offset need separate registers that do not alias with the
1034 // ones above.
1035 Register base = esi;
1036 Register offset = edi;
1037
1038 // Spill all these registers if they are still holding other values.
1039 __ SpillRegisters(old_hi, old_lo, new_hi, base, offset);
1040 if (offset_reg == no_reg) {
1041 if (dst_addr != base) __ mov(base, dst_addr);
1042 offset = no_reg;
1043 } else {
1044 // Potentially swap base and offset register to avoid unnecessary moves.
1045 if (dst_addr == offset || offset_reg == base) {
1046 std::swap(dst_addr, offset_reg);
1047 }
1048 __ ParallelRegisterMove(
1049 {{LiftoffRegister{base}, LiftoffRegister{dst_addr}, kI32},
1050 {LiftoffRegister{offset}, LiftoffRegister{offset_reg}, kI32}});
1051 }
1052
1053 Operand dst_op_lo = liftoff::MemOperand(base, offset, offset_imm);
1054 Operand dst_op_hi = liftoff::MemOperand(base, offset, offset_imm + 4);
1055
1056 // Load the old value from memory.
1057 __ mov(old_lo, dst_op_lo);
1058 __ mov(old_hi, dst_op_hi);
1059 Label retry;
1060 __ bind(&retry);
1061 __ mov(new_lo, old_lo);
1062 __ mov(new_hi, old_hi);
1063 switch (op) {
1064 case kAdd:
1065 __ add(new_lo, value_op_lo);
1066 __ adc(new_hi, value_op_hi);
1067 break;
1068 case kSub:
1069 __ sub(new_lo, value_op_lo);
1070 __ sbb(new_hi, value_op_hi);
1071 break;
1072 case kAnd:
1073 __ and_(new_lo, value_op_lo);
1074 __ and_(new_hi, value_op_hi);
1075 break;
1076 case kOr:
1077 __ or_(new_lo, value_op_lo);
1078 __ or_(new_hi, value_op_hi);
1079 break;
1080 case kXor:
1081 __ xor_(new_lo, value_op_lo);
1082 __ xor_(new_hi, value_op_hi);
1083 break;
1084 case kExchange:
1085 __ mov(new_lo, value_op_lo);
1086 __ mov(new_hi, value_op_hi);
1087 break;
1088 }
1089 __ lock();
1090 __ cmpxchg8b(dst_op_lo);
1091 __ j(not_equal, &retry);
1092
1093 // Deallocate the stack space again.
1094 __ add(esp, Immediate(8));
1095 // Restore the root register, and we are done.
1096 __ pop(kRootRegister);
1097
1098 // Move the result into the correct registers.
1099 __ ParallelRegisterMove(
1100 {{result, LiftoffRegister::ForPair(old_lo, old_hi), kI64}});
1101}

1103#undef __

1190void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicCompareExchange(
1191 Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg, uint32_t offset_imm,
1192 LiftoffRegister expected, LiftoffRegister new_value, LiftoffRegister result,
1193 StoreType type, bool /* i64_offset */) {
1194 // We expect that the offset has already been added to {dst_addr}, and no
1195 // {offset_reg} is provided. This is to save registers.
1196 DCHECK_EQ(offset_reg, no_reg);
1197
1198 DCHECK_EQ(result, expected);
1199
1200 if (type.value() != StoreType::kI64Store) {
1201 bool is_64_bit_op = type.value_type() == kWasmI64;
1202
1203 Register value_reg = is_64_bit_op ? new_value.low_gp() : new_value.gp();
1204 Register expected_reg = is_64_bit_op ? expected.low_gp() : expected.gp();
1205 Register result_reg = expected_reg;
1206
1207 // The cmpxchg instruction uses eax to store the old value of the
1208 // compare-exchange primitive. Therefore we have to spill the register and
1209 // move any use to another register.
1210 ClearRegister(eax, {&dst_addr, &value_reg},
1211 LiftoffRegList{dst_addr, value_reg, expected_reg});
1212 if (expected_reg != eax) {
1213 mov(eax, expected_reg);
1214 expected_reg = eax;
1215 }
1216
1217 bool is_byte_store = type.size() == 1;
1218 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, value_reg, expected_reg};
1219
1220 // Ensure that {value_reg} is a valid register.
1221 if (is_byte_store && !liftoff::kByteRegs.has(value_reg)) {
1222 Register safe_value_reg =
1223 pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(liftoff::kByteRegs.MaskOut(pinned)))
1224 .gp();
1225 mov(safe_value_reg, value_reg);
1226 value_reg = safe_value_reg;
1227 pinned.clear(LiftoffRegister(value_reg));
1228 }
1229
1230 Operand dst_op = Operand(dst_addr, offset_imm);
1231
1232 lock();
1233 switch (type.value()) {
1234 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1235 case StoreType::kI64Store8: {
1236 cmpxchg_b(dst_op, value_reg);
1237 movzx_b(result_reg, eax);
1238 break;
1239 }
1240 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1241 case StoreType::kI64Store16: {
1242 cmpxchg_w(dst_op, value_reg);
1243 movzx_w(result_reg, eax);
1244 break;
1245 }
1246 case StoreType::kI32Store:
1247 case StoreType::kI64Store32: {
1248 cmpxchg(dst_op, value_reg);
1249 if (result_reg != eax) {
1250 mov(result_reg, eax);
1251 }
1252 break;
1253 }
1254 default:
1255 UNREACHABLE();
1256 }
1257 if (is_64_bit_op) {
1258 xor_(result.high_gp(), result.high_gp());
1259 }
1260 return;
1261 }
1262
1263 // The following code handles kExprI64AtomicCompareExchange.
1264
1265 // We need {ebx} here, which is the root register. The root register it
1266 // needs special treatment. As we use {ebx} directly in the code below, we
1267 // have to make sure here that the root register is actually {ebx}.
1268 static_assert(kRootRegister == ebx,
1269 "The following code assumes that kRootRegister == ebx");
1270 push(kRootRegister);
1271
1272 // The compare-exchange instruction uses registers as follows:
1273 // old-value = EDX:EAX; new-value = ECX:EBX.
1274 Register expected_hi = edx;
1275 Register expected_lo = eax;
1276 Register new_hi = ecx;
1277 Register new_lo = ebx;
1278 // The address needs a separate registers that does not alias with the
1279 // ones above.
1280 Register address = esi;
1281
1282 // Spill all these registers if they are still holding other values.
1283 SpillRegisters(expected_hi, expected_lo, new_hi, address);
1284
1285 // We have to set new_lo specially, because it's the root register. We do it
1286 // before setting all other registers so that the original value does not get
1287 // overwritten.
1288 mov(new_lo, new_value.low_gp());
1289
1290 // Move all other values into the right register.
1291 ParallelRegisterMove(
1292 {{LiftoffRegister(address), LiftoffRegister(dst_addr), kI32},
1293 {LiftoffRegister::ForPair(expected_lo, expected_hi), expected, kI64},
1294 {LiftoffRegister(new_hi), new_value.high(), kI32}});
1295
1296 Operand dst_op = Operand(address, offset_imm);
1297
1298 lock();
1299 cmpxchg8b(dst_op);
1300
1301 // Restore the root register, and we are done.
1302 pop(kRootRegister);
1303
1304 // Move the result into the correct registers.
1305 ParallelRegisterMove(
1306 {{result, LiftoffRegister::ForPair(expected_lo, expected_hi), kI64}});
1307}

1331void LiftoffAssembler::MoveStackValue(uint32_t dst_offset, uint32_t src_offset,
1332 ValueKind kind) {
1333 DCHECK_EQ(0, SlotSizeForType(kind) % kSystemPointerSize);
1334 int words = SlotSizeForType(kind) / kSystemPointerSize;
1335 DCHECK_LE(1, words);
1336 // Make sure we move the words in the correct order in case there is an
1337 // overlap between src and dst.
1338 if (src_offset < dst_offset) {
1339 do {
1340 liftoff::MoveStackValue(this, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src_offset),
1341 liftoff::GetStackSlot(dst_offset));
1342 dst_offset -= kSystemPointerSize;
1343 src_offset -= kSystemPointerSize;
1344 } while (--words);
1345 } else {
1346 while (words--) {
1347 liftoff::MoveStackValue(
1348 this, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src_offset - words * kSystemPointerSize),
1349 liftoff::GetStackSlot(dst_offset - words * kSystemPointerSize));
1350 }
1351 }
1352}

1357 mov(dst, src);
1358}

1360void LiftoffAssembler::Move(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister src,
1361 ValueKind kind) {
1362 DCHECK_NE(dst, src);
1363 if (kind == kF32) {
1364 movss(dst, src);
1365 } else if (kind == kF64) {
1366 movsd(dst, src);
1367 } else {
1368 DCHECK_EQ(kS128, kind);
1369 Movaps(dst, src);
1370 }

1373void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, LiftoffRegister reg, ValueKind kind) {
1374 RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1375 Operand dst = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1376 switch (kind) {
1377 case kI32:
1378 case kRefNull:
1379 case kRef:
1380 case kRtt:
1381 mov(dst, reg.gp());
1382 break;
1383 case kI64:
1384 mov(liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(offset, kLowWord), reg.low_gp());
1385 mov(liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(offset, kHighWord), reg.high_gp());
1386 break;
1387 case kF32:
1388 movss(dst, reg.fp());
1389 break;
1390 case kF64:
1391 movsd(dst, reg.fp());
1392 break;
1393 case kS128:
1394 movdqu(dst, reg.fp());
1395 break;
1396 default:
1397 UNREACHABLE();
1398 }
1399}
1400
1401void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, WasmValue value) {
1402 RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1403 Operand dst = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1404 switch (value.type().kind()) {
1405 case kI32:
1406 mov(dst, Immediate(value.to_i32()));
1407 break;
1408 case kI64: {
1409 int32_t low_word = value.to_i64();
1410 int32_t high_word = value.to_i64() >> 32;
1411 mov(liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(offset, kLowWord), Immediate(low_word));
1412 mov(liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(offset, kHighWord), Immediate(high_word));
1413 break;
1414 }
1415 default:
1416 // We do not track f32 and f64 constants, hence they are unreachable.
1417 UNREACHABLE();
1418 }
1419}

1428
1429void LiftoffAssembler::FillStackSlotsWithZero(int start, int size) {
1430 DCHECK_LT(0, size);
1431 DCHECK_EQ(0, size % 4);
1432 RecordUsedSpillOffset(start + size);
1433
1434 if (size <= 12) {
1435 // Special straight-line code for up to three words (6-9 bytes per word:
1436 // C7 <1-4 bytes operand> <4 bytes imm>, makes 18-27 bytes total).
1437 for (int offset = 4; offset <= size; offset += 4) {
1438 mov(liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(start + offset, kLowWord), Immediate(0));
1439 }
1440 } else {
1441 // General case for bigger counts.
1442 // This sequence takes 19-22 bytes (3 for pushes, 3-6 for lea, 2 for xor, 5
1443 // for mov, 3 for repstosq, 3 for pops).
1444 // Note: rep_stos fills ECX doublewords at [EDI] with EAX.
1445 push(eax);
1446 push(ecx);
1447 push(edi);
1448 lea(edi, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + size));
1449 xor_(eax, eax);
1450 // Size is in bytes, convert to doublewords (4-bytes).
1451 mov(ecx, Immediate(size / 4));
1452 rep_stos();
1453 pop(edi);
1454 pop(ecx);
1455 pop(eax);
1456 }
1457}

1460 ValueKind /* kind */) {

1462}

1480void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_sub(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs) {
1481 if (dst != rhs) {
1482 // Default path.
1483 if (dst != lhs) mov(dst, lhs);
1484 sub(dst, rhs);
1485 } else if (lhs == rhs) {
1486 // Degenerate case.
1487 xor_(dst, dst);

1492 }

1507void EmitCommutativeBinOp(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register dst, Register lhs,
1508 Register rhs) {
1509 if (dst == rhs) {
1510 (assm->*op)(dst, lhs);
1511 } else {
1512 if (dst != lhs) assm->mov(dst, lhs);
1513 (assm->*op)(dst, rhs);
1514 }
1515}

1522}

1537namespace liftoff {
1538enum class DivOrRem : uint8_t { kDiv, kRem };
1539template <bool is_signed, DivOrRem div_or_rem>
1540void EmitInt32DivOrRem(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register dst, Register lhs,
1541 Register rhs, Label* trap_div_by_zero,
1542 Label* trap_div_unrepresentable) {
1543 constexpr bool needs_unrepresentable_check =
1544 is_signed && div_or_rem == DivOrRem::kDiv;
1545 constexpr bool special_case_minus_1 =
1546 is_signed && div_or_rem == DivOrRem::kRem;
1547 DCHECK_EQ(needs_unrepresentable_check, trap_div_unrepresentable != nullptr);
1548
1549 // For division, the lhs is always taken from {edx:eax}. Thus, make sure that
1550 // these registers are unused. If {rhs} is stored in one of them, move it to
1551 // another temporary register.
1552 // Do all this before any branch, such that the code is executed
1553 // unconditionally, as the cache state will also be modified unconditionally.
1554 assm->SpillRegisters(eax, edx);
1555 if (rhs == eax || rhs == edx) {
1556 LiftoffRegList unavailable{eax, edx, lhs};
1557 Register tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, unavailable).gp();
1558 assm->mov(tmp, rhs);
1559 rhs = tmp;
1560 }
1561
1562 // Check for division by zero.
1563 assm->test(rhs, rhs);
1564 assm->j(zero, trap_div_by_zero);
1565
1566 Label done;
1567 if (needs_unrepresentable_check) {
1568 // Check for {kMinInt / -1}. This is unrepresentable.
1569 Label do_div;
1570 assm->cmp(rhs, -1);
1571 assm->j(not_equal, &do_div);
1572 assm->cmp(lhs, kMinInt);
1573 assm->j(equal, trap_div_unrepresentable);
1574 assm->bind(&do_div);
1575 } else if (special_case_minus_1) {
1576 // {lhs % -1} is always 0 (needs to be special cased because {kMinInt / -1}
1577 // cannot be computed).
1578 Label do_rem;
1579 assm->cmp(rhs, -1);
1580 assm->j(not_equal, &do_rem);
1581 assm->xor_(dst, dst);
1582 assm->jmp(&done);
1583 assm->bind(&do_rem);
1584 }
1585
1586 // Now move {lhs} into {eax}, then zero-extend or sign-extend into {edx}, then
1587 // do the division.
1588 if (lhs != eax) assm->mov(eax, lhs);
1589 if (is_signed) {
1590 assm->cdq();
1591 assm->idiv(rhs);
1592 } else {
1593 assm->xor_(edx, edx);
1594 assm->div(rhs);
1595 }
1596
1597 // Move back the result (in {eax} or {edx}) into the {dst} register.
1598 constexpr Register kResultReg = div_or_rem == DivOrRem::kDiv ? eax : edx;
1599 if (dst != kResultReg) assm->mov(dst, kResultReg);
1600 if (special_case_minus_1) assm->bind(&done);
1601}
1602} // namespace liftoff

1653namespace liftoff {
1654inline void EmitShiftOperation(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register dst,
1655 Register src, Register amount,
1656 void (Assembler::*emit_shift)(Register)) {
1657 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst, src, amount};
1658 // If dst is ecx, compute into a tmp register first, then move to ecx.
1659 if (dst == ecx) {
1660 Register tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1661 assm->mov(tmp, src);
1662 if (amount != ecx) assm->mov(ecx, amount);
1663 (assm->*emit_shift)(tmp);
1664 assm->mov(ecx, tmp);
1665 return;
1666 }
1667
1668 // Move amount into ecx. If ecx is in use, move its content to a tmp register
1669 // first. If src is ecx, src is now the tmp register.
1670 Register tmp_reg = no_reg;
1671 if (amount != ecx) {
1672 if (assm->cache_state()->is_used(LiftoffRegister(ecx)) ||
1673 pinned.has(LiftoffRegister(ecx))) {
1674 tmp_reg = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1675 assm->mov(tmp_reg, ecx);
1676 if (src == ecx) src = tmp_reg;
1677 }
1678 assm->mov(ecx, amount);
1679 }
1680
1681 // Do the actual shift.
1682 if (dst != src) assm->mov(dst, src);
1683 (assm->*emit_shift)(dst);
1684
1685 // Restore ecx if needed.
1686 if (tmp_reg.is_valid()) assm->mov(ecx, tmp_reg);
1687}
1688} // namespace liftoff

1739template <void (Assembler::*op)(Register, Register),
1740 void (Assembler::*op_with_carry)(Register, Register)>
1741inline void OpWithCarry(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
1742 LiftoffRegister lhs, LiftoffRegister rhs) {
1743 // First, compute the low half of the result, potentially into a temporary dst
1744 // register if {dst.low_gp()} equals {rhs.low_gp()} or any register we need to
1745 // keep alive for computing the upper half.
1746 LiftoffRegList keep_alive{lhs.high_gp(), rhs};
1747 Register dst_low = keep_alive.has(dst.low_gp())
1748 ? assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, keep_alive).gp()
1749 : dst.low_gp();
1750
1751 if (dst_low != lhs.low_gp()) assm->mov(dst_low, lhs.low_gp());
1752 (assm->*op)(dst_low, rhs.low_gp());
1753
1754 // Now compute the upper half, while keeping alive the previous result.
1755 keep_alive = LiftoffRegList{dst_low, rhs.high_gp()};
1756 Register dst_high = keep_alive.has(dst.high_gp())
1757 ? assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, keep_alive).gp()
1758 : dst.high_gp();
1759
1760 if (dst_high != lhs.high_gp()) assm->mov(dst_high, lhs.high_gp());
1761 (assm->*op_with_carry)(dst_high, rhs.high_gp());
1762
1763 // If necessary, move result into the right registers.
1764 LiftoffRegister tmp_result = LiftoffRegister::ForPair(dst_low, dst_high);
1765 if (tmp_result != dst) assm->Move(dst, tmp_result, kI64);
1766}
1767
1768template <void (Assembler::*op)(Register, const Immediate&),
1769 void (Assembler::*op_with_carry)(Register, int32_t)>
1770inline void OpWithCarryI(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
1771 LiftoffRegister lhs, int64_t imm) {
1772 // The compiler allocated registers such that either {dst == lhs} or there is
1773 // no overlap between the two.
1774 DCHECK_NE(dst.low_gp(), lhs.high_gp());
1775
1776 int32_t imm_low_word = static_cast<int32_t>(imm);
1777 int32_t imm_high_word = static_cast<int32_t>(imm >> 32);
1778
1779 // First, compute the low half of the result.
1780 if (dst.low_gp() != lhs.low_gp()) assm->mov(dst.low_gp(), lhs.low_gp());
1781 (assm->*op)(dst.low_gp(), Immediate(imm_low_word));
1782
1783 // Now compute the upper half.
1784 if (dst.high_gp() != lhs.high_gp()) assm->mov(dst.high_gp(), lhs.high_gp());
1785 (assm->*op_with_carry)(dst.high_gp(), imm_high_word);
1786}
1787} // namespace liftoff

1803
1804void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_mul(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
1805 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
1806 // Idea:
1807 // [ lhs_hi | lhs_lo ] * [ rhs_hi | rhs_lo ]
1808 // = [ lhs_hi * rhs_lo | ] (32 bit mul, shift 32)
1809 // + [ lhs_lo * rhs_hi | ] (32 bit mul, shift 32)
1810 // + [ lhs_lo * rhs_lo ] (32x32->64 mul, shift 0)
1811
1812 // For simplicity, we move lhs and rhs into fixed registers.
1813 Register dst_hi = edx;
1814 Register dst_lo = eax;
1815 Register lhs_hi = ecx;
1816 Register lhs_lo = dst_lo;
1817 Register rhs_hi = dst_hi;
1818 Register rhs_lo = esi;
1819
1820 // Spill all these registers if they are still holding other values.
1821 SpillRegisters(dst_hi, dst_lo, lhs_hi, rhs_lo);
1822
1823 // Move lhs and rhs into the respective registers.
1824 ParallelRegisterMove({{LiftoffRegister::ForPair(lhs_lo, lhs_hi), lhs, kI64},
1825 {LiftoffRegister::ForPair(rhs_lo, rhs_hi), rhs, kI64}});
1826
1827 // First mul: lhs_hi' = lhs_hi * rhs_lo.
1828 imul(lhs_hi, rhs_lo);
1829 // Second mul: rhi_hi' = rhs_hi * lhs_lo.
1830 imul(rhs_hi, lhs_lo);
1831 // Add them: lhs_hi'' = lhs_hi' + rhs_hi' = lhs_hi * rhs_lo + rhs_hi * lhs_lo.
1832 add(lhs_hi, rhs_hi);
1833 // Third mul: edx:eax (dst_hi:dst_lo) = eax * esi (lhs_lo * rhs_lo).
1834 mul(rhs_lo);
1835 // Add lhs_hi'' to dst_hi.
1836 add(dst_hi, lhs_hi);
1837
1838 // Finally, move back the temporary result to the actual dst register pair.
1839 LiftoffRegister dst_tmp = LiftoffRegister::ForPair(dst_lo, dst_hi);
1840 if (dst != dst_tmp) Move(dst, dst_tmp, kI64);
1841}

1868namespace liftoff {
1869inline bool PairContains(LiftoffRegister pair, Register reg) {
1870 return pair.low_gp() == reg || pair.high_gp() == reg;
1871}
1872
1873inline LiftoffRegister ReplaceInPair(LiftoffRegister pair, Register old_reg,
1874 Register new_reg) {
1875 if (pair.low_gp() == old_reg) {
1876 return LiftoffRegister::ForPair(new_reg, pair.high_gp());
1877 }
1878 if (pair.high_gp() == old_reg) {
1879 return LiftoffRegister::ForPair(pair.low_gp(), new_reg);
1880 }
1881 return pair;
1882}
1883
1884inline void Emit64BitShiftOperation(
1885 LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src,
1886 Register amount, void (MacroAssembler::*emit_shift)(Register, Register)) {
1887 // Temporary registers cannot overlap with {dst}.
1888 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst};
1889
1890 constexpr size_t kMaxRegMoves = 3;
1891 base::SmallVector<LiftoffAssembler::ParallelRegisterMoveTuple, kMaxRegMoves>
1892 reg_moves;
1893
1894 // If {dst} contains {ecx}, replace it by an unused register, which is then
1895 // moved to {ecx} in the end.
1896 Register ecx_replace = no_reg;
1897 if (PairContains(dst, ecx)) {
1898 ecx_replace = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1899 dst = ReplaceInPair(dst, ecx, ecx_replace);
1900 // If {amount} needs to be moved to {ecx}, but {ecx} is in use (and not part
1901 // of {dst}, hence overwritten anyway), move {ecx} to a tmp register and
1902 // restore it at the end.
1903 } else if (amount != ecx &&
1904 (assm->cache_state()->is_used(LiftoffRegister(ecx)) ||
1905 pinned.has(LiftoffRegister(ecx)))) {
1906 ecx_replace = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1907 reg_moves.emplace_back(ecx_replace, ecx, kI32);
1908 }
1909
1910 reg_moves.emplace_back(dst, src, kI64);
1911 reg_moves.emplace_back(ecx, amount, kI32);
1912 assm->ParallelRegisterMove(base::VectorOf(reg_moves));
1913
1914 // Do the actual shift.
1915 (assm->*emit_shift)(dst.high_gp(), dst.low_gp());
1916
1917 // Restore {ecx} if needed.
1918 if (ecx_replace != no_reg) assm->mov(ecx, ecx_replace);
1919}
1920} // namespace liftoff

1929 int32_t amount) {
1930 amount &= 63;
1931 if (amount >= 32) {
1932 if (dst.high_gp() != src.low_gp()) mov(dst.high_gp(), src.low_gp());
1933 if (amount != 32) shl(dst.high_gp(), amount - 32);
1934 xor_(dst.low_gp(), dst.low_gp());
1935 } else {
1936 if (dst != src) Move(dst, src, kI64);
1937 ShlPair(dst.high_gp(), dst.low_gp(), amount);

1979void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_clz(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src) {
1980 // return high == 0 ? 32 + CLZ32(low) : CLZ32(high);
1981 Label done;
1982 Register safe_dst = dst.low_gp();
1983 if (src.low_gp() == safe_dst) safe_dst = dst.high_gp();
1984 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LZCNT)) {
1985 CpuFeatureScope scope(this, LZCNT);
1986 lzcnt(safe_dst, src.high_gp()); // Sets CF if high == 0.
1987 j(not_carry, &done, Label::kNear);
1988 lzcnt(safe_dst, src.low_gp());
1989 add(safe_dst, Immediate(32)); // 32 + CLZ32(low)
1990 } else {
1991 // CLZ32(x) =^ x == 0 ? 32 : 31 - BSR32(x)
1992 Label high_is_zero;
1993 bsr(safe_dst, src.high_gp()); // Sets ZF is high == 0.
1994 j(zero, &high_is_zero, Label::kNear);
1995 xor_(safe_dst, Immediate(31)); // for x in [0..31], 31^x == 31-x.
1996 jmp(&done, Label::kNear);
1997
1998 bind(&high_is_zero);
1999 Label low_not_zero;
2000 bsr(safe_dst, src.low_gp());
2001 j(not_zero, &low_not_zero, Label::kNear);
2002 mov(safe_dst, Immediate(64 ^ 63)); // 64, after the xor below.
2003 bind(&low_not_zero);
2004 xor_(safe_dst, 63); // for x in [0..31], 63^x == 63-x.
2005 }
2006
2007 bind(&done);
2008 if (safe_dst != dst.low_gp()) mov(dst.low_gp(), safe_dst);
2009 xor_(dst.high_gp(), dst.high_gp()); // High word of result is always 0.
2010}
2011
2012void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_ctz(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src) {
2013 // return low == 0 ? 32 + CTZ32(high) : CTZ32(low);
2014 Label done;
2015 Register safe_dst = dst.low_gp();
2016 if (src.high_gp() == safe_dst) safe_dst = dst.high_gp();
2017 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(BMI1)) {
2018 CpuFeatureScope scope(this, BMI1);
2019 tzcnt(safe_dst, src.low_gp()); // Sets CF if low == 0.
2020 j(not_carry, &done, Label::kNear);
2021 tzcnt(safe_dst, src.high_gp());
2022 add(safe_dst, Immediate(32)); // 32 + CTZ32(high)
2023 } else {
2024 // CTZ32(x) =^ x == 0 ? 32 : BSF32(x)
2025 bsf(safe_dst, src.low_gp()); // Sets ZF is low == 0.
2026 j(not_zero, &done, Label::kNear);
2027
2028 Label high_not_zero;
2029 bsf(safe_dst, src.high_gp());
2030 j(not_zero, &high_not_zero, Label::kNear);
2031 mov(safe_dst, 64); // low == 0 and high == 0
2032 jmp(&done);
2033 bind(&high_not_zero);
2034 add(safe_dst, Immediate(32)); // 32 + CTZ32(high)
2035 }
2036
2037 bind(&done);
2038 if (safe_dst != dst.low_gp()) mov(dst.low_gp(), safe_dst);
2039 xor_(dst.high_gp(), dst.high_gp()); // High word of result is always 0.
2040}
2041
2042bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_popcnt(LiftoffRegister dst,
2043 LiftoffRegister src) {
2044 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(POPCNT)) return false;
2045 CpuFeatureScope scope(this, POPCNT);
2046 // Produce partial popcnts in the two dst registers.
2047 Register src1 = src.high_gp() == dst.low_gp() ? src.high_gp() : src.low_gp();
2048 Register src2 = src.high_gp() == dst.low_gp() ? src.low_gp() : src.high_gp();
2049 popcnt(dst.low_gp(), src1);
2050 popcnt(dst.high_gp(), src2);
2051 // Add the two into the lower dst reg, clear the higher dst reg.
2052 add(dst.low_gp(), dst.high_gp());
2053 xor_(dst.high_gp(), dst.high_gp());
2054 return true;
2055}

2117namespace liftoff {
2118enum class MinOrMax : uint8_t { kMin, kMax };
2119template <typename type>
2120inline void EmitFloatMinOrMax(LiftoffAssembler* assm, DoubleRegister dst,
2121 DoubleRegister lhs, DoubleRegister rhs,
2122 MinOrMax min_or_max) {
2123 Label is_nan;
2124 Label lhs_below_rhs;
2125 Label lhs_above_rhs;
2126 Label done;
2127
2128 // We need one tmp register to extract the sign bit. Get it right at the
2129 // beginning, such that the spilling code is not accidentially jumped over.
2130 Register tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {}).gp();
2131
2132#define dop(name, ...) \
2133 do { \
2134 if (sizeof(type) == 4) { \
2135 assm->name##s(__VA_ARGS__); \
2136 } else { \
2137 assm->name##d(__VA_ARGS__); \
2138 } \
2139 } while (false)
2140
2141 // Check the easy cases first: nan (e.g. unordered), smaller and greater.
2142 // NaN has to be checked first, because PF=1 implies CF=1.
2143 dop(ucomis, lhs, rhs);
2144 assm->j(parity_even, &is_nan, Label::kNear); // PF=1
2145 assm->j(below, &lhs_below_rhs, Label::kNear); // CF=1
2146 assm->j(above, &lhs_above_rhs, Label::kNear); // CF=0 && ZF=0
2147
2148 // If we get here, then either
2149 // a) {lhs == rhs},
2150 // b) {lhs == -0.0} and {rhs == 0.0}, or
2151 // c) {lhs == 0.0} and {rhs == -0.0}.
2152 // For a), it does not matter whether we return {lhs} or {rhs}. Check the sign
2153 // bit of {rhs} to differentiate b) and c).
2154 dop(movmskp, tmp, rhs);
2155 assm->test(tmp, Immediate(1));
2156 assm->j(zero, &lhs_below_rhs, Label::kNear);
2157 assm->jmp(&lhs_above_rhs, Label::kNear);
2158
2159 assm->bind(&is_nan);
2160 // Create a NaN output.
2161 dop(xorp, dst, dst);
2162 dop(divs, dst, dst);
2163 assm->jmp(&done, Label::kNear);
2164
2165 assm->bind(&lhs_below_rhs);
2166 DoubleRegister lhs_below_rhs_src = min_or_max == MinOrMax::kMin ? lhs : rhs;
2167 if (dst != lhs_below_rhs_src) dop(movs, dst, lhs_below_rhs_src);
2168 assm->jmp(&done, Label::kNear);
2169
2170 assm->bind(&lhs_above_rhs);
2171 DoubleRegister lhs_above_rhs_src = min_or_max == MinOrMax::kMin ? rhs : lhs;
2172 if (dst != lhs_above_rhs_src) dop(movs, dst, lhs_above_rhs_src);
2173
2174 assm->bind(&done);
2175}
2176} // namespace liftoff

2190void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_copysign(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
2191 DoubleRegister rhs) {
2192 static constexpr int kF32SignBit = 1 << 31;
2193 LiftoffRegList pinned;
2194 Register scratch = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
2195 Register scratch2 = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
2196 Movd(scratch, lhs); // move {lhs} into {scratch}.
2197 and_(scratch, Immediate(~kF32SignBit)); // clear sign bit in {scratch}.
2198 Movd(scratch2, rhs); // move {rhs} into {scratch2}.
2199 and_(scratch2, Immediate(kF32SignBit)); // isolate sign bit in {scratch2}.
2200 or_(scratch, scratch2); // combine {scratch2} into {scratch}.
2201 Movd(dst, scratch); // move result into {dst}.
2202}

2317void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_copysign(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
2318 DoubleRegister rhs) {
2319 static constexpr int kF32SignBit = 1 << 31;
2320 // On ia32, we cannot hold the whole f64 value in a gp register, so we just
2321 // operate on the upper half (UH).

2323 Register scratch = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
2324 Register scratch2 = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
2325
2326 Pextrd(scratch, lhs, 1); // move UH of {lhs} into {scratch}.

2393#define __ assm->
2394// Used for float to int conversions. If the value in {converted_back} equals
2395// {src} afterwards, the conversion succeeded.
2396template <typename dst_type, typename src_type>
2397inline void ConvertFloatToIntAndBack(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register dst,
2398 DoubleRegister src,
2399 DoubleRegister converted_back,
2400 LiftoffRegList pinned) {
2401 if (std::is_same<double, src_type>::value) { // f64
2402 if (std::is_signed<dst_type>::value) { // f64 -> i32
2403 __ cvttsd2si(dst, src);
2404 __ Cvtsi2sd(converted_back, dst);
2405 } else { // f64 -> u32
2406 __ Cvttsd2ui(dst, src, liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
2407 __ Cvtui2sd(converted_back, dst,
2408 __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp());
2409 }
2410 } else { // f32
2411 if (std::is_signed<dst_type>::value) { // f32 -> i32
2412 __ cvttss2si(dst, src);
2413 __ Cvtsi2ss(converted_back, dst);
2414 } else { // f32 -> u32
2415 __ Cvttss2ui(dst, src, liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
2416 __ Cvtui2ss(converted_back, dst,
2417 __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp());
2418 }
2419 }
2420}
2421
2422template <typename dst_type, typename src_type>
2423inline bool EmitTruncateFloatToInt(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register dst,
2424 DoubleRegister src, Label* trap) {
2425 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SSE4_1)) {
2426 __ bailout(kMissingCPUFeature, "no SSE4.1");
2427 return true;
2428 }
2429 CpuFeatureScope feature(assm, SSE4_1);
2430
2431 LiftoffRegList pinned{src, dst};
2432 DoubleRegister rounded =
2433 pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, pinned)).fp();
2434 DoubleRegister converted_back =
2435 pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, pinned)).fp();
2436
2437 if (std::is_same<double, src_type>::value) { // f64
2438 __ roundsd(rounded, src, kRoundToZero);
2439 } else { // f32
2440 __ roundss(rounded, src, kRoundToZero);
2441 }
2442 ConvertFloatToIntAndBack<dst_type, src_type>(assm, dst, rounded,
2443 converted_back, pinned);
2444 if (std::is_same<double, src_type>::value) { // f64
2445 __ ucomisd(converted_back, rounded);
2446 } else { // f32
2447 __ ucomiss(converted_back, rounded);
2448 }
2449
2450 // Jump to trap if PF is 0 (one of the operands was NaN) or they are not
2451 // equal.
2452 __ j(parity_even, trap);
2453 __ j(not_equal, trap);
2454 return true;
2455}
2456
2457template <typename dst_type, typename src_type>
2458inline bool EmitSatTruncateFloatToInt(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register dst,
2459 DoubleRegister src) {
2460 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SSE4_1)) {
2461 __ bailout(kMissingCPUFeature, "no SSE4.1");
2462 return true;
2463 }
2464 CpuFeatureScope feature(assm, SSE4_1);
2465
2466 Label done;
2467 Label not_nan;
2468 Label src_positive;
2469
2470 LiftoffRegList pinned{src, dst};
2471 DoubleRegister rounded =
2472 pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, pinned)).fp();
2473 DoubleRegister converted_back =
2474 pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, pinned)).fp();
2475 DoubleRegister zero_reg =
2476 pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, pinned)).fp();
2477
2478 if (std::is_same<double, src_type>::value) { // f64
2479 __ roundsd(rounded, src, kRoundToZero);
2480 } else { // f32
2481 __ roundss(rounded, src, kRoundToZero);
2482 }
2483
2484 ConvertFloatToIntAndBack<dst_type, src_type>(assm, dst, rounded,
2485 converted_back, pinned);
2486 if (std::is_same<double, src_type>::value) { // f64
2487 __ ucomisd(converted_back, rounded);
2488 } else { // f32
2489 __ ucomiss(converted_back, rounded);
2490 }
2491
2492 // Return 0 if PF is 0 (one of the operands was NaN)
2493 __ j(parity_odd, &not_nan);
2494 __ xor_(dst, dst);
2495 __ jmp(&done);
2496
2497 __ bind(&not_nan);
2498 // If rounding is as expected, return result
2499 __ j(equal, &done);
2500
2501 __ Xorpd(zero_reg, zero_reg);
2502
2503 // if out-of-bounds, check if src is positive
2504 if (std::is_same<double, src_type>::value) { // f64
2505 __ ucomisd(src, zero_reg);
2506 } else { // f32
2507 __ ucomiss(src, zero_reg);
2508 }
2509 __ j(above, &src_positive);
2510 __ mov(dst, Immediate(std::numeric_limits<dst_type>::min()));
2511 __ jmp(&done);
2512
2513 __ bind(&src_positive);
2514
2515 __ mov(dst, Immediate(std::numeric_limits<dst_type>::max()));
2516
2517 __ bind(&done);
2518 return true;
2519}
2520#undef __
2521} // namespace liftoff

2523bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_type_conversion(WasmOpcode opcode,
2524 LiftoffRegister dst,
2525 LiftoffRegister src, Label* trap) {
2526 switch (opcode) {
2527 case kExprI32ConvertI64:
2528 if (dst.gp() != src.low_gp()) mov(dst.gp(), src.low_gp());
2529 return true;
2530 case kExprI32SConvertF32:
2531 return liftoff::EmitTruncateFloatToInt<int32_t, float>(this, dst.gp(),
2532 src.fp(), trap);
2533 case kExprI32UConvertF32:
2534 return liftoff::EmitTruncateFloatToInt<uint32_t, float>(this, dst.gp(),
2535 src.fp(), trap);
2536 case kExprI32SConvertF64:
2537 return liftoff::EmitTruncateFloatToInt<int32_t, double>(this, dst.gp(),
2538 src.fp(), trap);
2539 case kExprI32UConvertF64:
2540 return liftoff::EmitTruncateFloatToInt<uint32_t, double>(this, dst.gp(),
2541 src.fp(), trap);
2542 case kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
2543 return liftoff::EmitSatTruncateFloatToInt<int32_t, float>(this, dst.gp(),
2544 src.fp());
2545 case kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
2546 return liftoff::EmitSatTruncateFloatToInt<uint32_t, float>(this, dst.gp(),
2547 src.fp());
2548 case kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
2549 return liftoff::EmitSatTruncateFloatToInt<int32_t, double>(this, dst.gp(),
2550 src.fp());
2551 case kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
2552 return liftoff::EmitSatTruncateFloatToInt<uint32_t, double>(
2553 this, dst.gp(), src.fp());
2554 case kExprI32ReinterpretF32:
2555 Movd(dst.gp(), src.fp());
2556 return true;
2557 case kExprI64SConvertI32:
2558 if (dst.low_gp() != src.gp()) mov(dst.low_gp(), src.gp());
2559 if (dst.high_gp() != src.gp()) mov(dst.high_gp(), src.gp());
2560 sar(dst.high_gp(), 31);
2561 return true;
2562 case kExprI64UConvertI32:
2563 if (dst.low_gp() != src.gp()) mov(dst.low_gp(), src.gp());
2564 xor_(dst.high_gp(), dst.high_gp());
2565 return true;
2566 case kExprI64ReinterpretF64:
2567 // Push src to the stack.
2568 AllocateStackSpace(8);
2569 movsd(Operand(esp, 0), src.fp());
2570 // Pop to dst.
2571 pop(dst.low_gp());
2572 pop(dst.high_gp());
2573 return true;
2574 case kExprF32SConvertI32:
2575 cvtsi2ss(dst.fp(), src.gp());
2576 return true;
2577 case kExprF32UConvertI32: {
2578 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst, src};
2579 Register scratch = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
2580 Cvtui2ss(dst.fp(), src.gp(), scratch);
2581 return true;
2582 }
2583 case kExprF32ConvertF64:
2584 cvtsd2ss(dst.fp(), src.fp());
2585 return true;
2586 case kExprF32ReinterpretI32:
2587 Movd(dst.fp(), src.gp());
2588 return true;
2589 case kExprF64SConvertI32:
2590 Cvtsi2sd(dst.fp(), src.gp());
2591 return true;
2592 case kExprF64UConvertI32: {
2593 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst, src};
2594 Register scratch = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
2595 Cvtui2sd(dst.fp(), src.gp(), scratch);
2596 return true;
2597 }
2598 case kExprF64ConvertF32:
2599 cvtss2sd(dst.fp(), src.fp());
2600 return true;
2601 case kExprF64ReinterpretI64:
2602 // Push src to the stack.
2603 push(src.high_gp());
2604 push(src.low_gp());
2605 // Pop to dst.
2606 movsd(dst.fp(), Operand(esp, 0));
2607 add(esp, Immediate(8));
2608 return true;
2609 default:
2610 return false;
2611 }
2612}

2648void LiftoffAssembler::emit_cond_jump(Condition cond, Label* label,
2649 ValueKind kind, Register lhs,
2650 Register rhs,
2651 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
2652 if (rhs != no_reg) {
2653 switch (kind) {
2654 case kRef:
2655 case kRefNull:
2656 case kRtt:
2657 DCHECK(cond == kEqual || cond == kNotEqual);
2658 [[fallthrough]];
2659 case kI32:
2660 cmp(lhs, rhs);
2661 break;
2662 default:
2663 UNREACHABLE();
2664 }
2665 } else {
2666 DCHECK_EQ(kind, kI32);
2667 test(lhs, lhs);
2668 }
2669
2670 j(cond, label);
2671}

2675 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {

2677 j(cond, label);
2678}

2709void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_eqz(Register dst, LiftoffRegister src) {
2710 // Compute the OR of both registers in the src pair, using dst as scratch
2711 // register. Then check whether the result is equal to zero.
2712 if (src.low_gp() == dst) {
2713 or_(dst, src.high_gp());
2714 } else {
2715 if (src.high_gp() != dst) mov(dst, src.high_gp());
2716 or_(dst, src.low_gp());
2717 }
2718 liftoff::setcc_32(this, equal, dst);
2719}

2722inline Condition cond_make_unsigned(Condition cond) {
2723 switch (cond) {
2724 case kLessThan:
2725 return kUnsignedLessThan;
2726 case kLessThanEqual:
2727 return kUnsignedLessThanEqual;
2728 case kGreaterThan:
2729 return kUnsignedGreaterThan;
2730 case kGreaterThanEqual:
2731 return kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual;
2732 default:
2733 return cond;
2734 }
2735}
2736} // namespace liftoff
2737
2738void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond(Condition cond, Register dst,
2739 LiftoffRegister lhs,
2740 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2741 Condition unsigned_cond = liftoff::cond_make_unsigned(cond);
2742
2743 // Get the tmp byte register out here, such that we don't conditionally spill
2744 // (this cannot be reflected in the cache state).
2745 Register tmp_byte_reg = liftoff::GetTmpByteRegister(this, dst);
2746
2747 // For signed i64 comparisons, we still need to use unsigned comparison for
2748 // the low word (the only bit carrying signedness information is the MSB in
2749 // the high word).
2750 Label setcc;
2751 Label cont;
2752 // Compare high word first. If it differs, use if for the setcc. If it's
2753 // equal, compare the low word and use that for setcc.
2754 cmp(lhs.high_gp(), rhs.high_gp());
2755 j(not_equal, &setcc, Label::kNear);
2756 cmp(lhs.low_gp(), rhs.low_gp());
2757 if (unsigned_cond != cond) {
2758 // If the condition predicate for the low differs from that for the high
2759 // word, emit a separete setcc sequence for the low word.
2760 liftoff::setcc_32_no_spill(this, unsigned_cond, dst, tmp_byte_reg);
2761 jmp(&cont);
2762 }
2763 bind(&setcc);
2764 liftoff::setcc_32_no_spill(this, cond, dst, tmp_byte_reg);
2765 bind(&cont);
2766}

2769template <void (Assembler::*cmp_op)(DoubleRegister, DoubleRegister)>
2770void EmitFloatSetCond(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Condition cond, Register dst,
2771 DoubleRegister lhs, DoubleRegister rhs) {
2772 Label cont;
2773 Label not_nan;
2774
2775 // Get the tmp byte register out here, such that we don't conditionally spill
2776 // (this cannot be reflected in the cache state).
2777 Register tmp_byte_reg = GetTmpByteRegister(assm, dst);
2778
2779 (assm->*cmp_op)(lhs, rhs);
2780 // If PF is one, one of the operands was Nan. This needs special handling.
2781 assm->j(parity_odd, &not_nan, Label::kNear);
2782 // Return 1 for f32.ne, 0 for all other cases.
2783 if (cond == not_equal) {
2784 assm->mov(dst, Immediate(1));
2785 } else {
2786 assm->xor_(dst, dst);
2787 }
2788 assm->jmp(&cont, Label::kNear);
2789 assm->bind(&not_nan);
2790
2791 setcc_32_no_spill(assm, cond, dst, tmp_byte_reg);
2792 assm->bind(&cont);
2793}

2824template <void (Assembler::*avx_op)(XMMRegister, XMMRegister, XMMRegister),
2825 void (Assembler::*sse_op)(XMMRegister, XMMRegister)>
2826void EmitSimdCommutativeBinOp(
2827 LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
2828 LiftoffRegister rhs, std::optional<CpuFeature> feature = std::nullopt) {
2829 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
2830 CpuFeatureScope scope(assm, AVX);
2831 (assm->*avx_op)(dst.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp());
2832 return;
2833 }
2834
2835 std::optional<CpuFeatureScope> sse_scope;
2836 if (feature.has_value()) sse_scope.emplace(assm, *feature);
2837
2838 if (dst.fp() == rhs.fp()) {
2839 (assm->*sse_op)(dst.fp(), lhs.fp());
2840 } else {
2841 if (dst.fp() != lhs.fp()) (assm->movaps)(dst.fp(), lhs.fp());
2842 (assm->*sse_op)(dst.fp(), rhs.fp());
2843 }
2844}
2845
2846template <void (Assembler::*avx_op)(XMMRegister, XMMRegister, XMMRegister),
2847 void (Assembler::*sse_op)(XMMRegister, XMMRegister)>
2848void EmitSimdNonCommutativeBinOp(
2849 LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
2850 LiftoffRegister rhs, std::optional<CpuFeature> feature = std::nullopt) {
2851 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
2852 CpuFeatureScope scope(assm, AVX);
2853 (assm->*avx_op)(dst.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp());
2854 return;
2855 }
2856
2857 std::optional<CpuFeatureScope> sse_scope;
2858 if (feature.has_value()) sse_scope.emplace(assm, *feature);
2859
2860 if (dst.fp() == rhs.fp()) {
2861 assm->movaps(kScratchDoubleReg, rhs.fp());
2862 assm->movaps(dst.fp(), lhs.fp());
2863 (assm->*sse_op)(dst.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
2864 } else {
2865 if (dst.fp() != lhs.fp()) assm->movaps(dst.fp(), lhs.fp());
2866 (assm->*sse_op)(dst.fp(), rhs.fp());
2867 }
2868}

2870template <void (Assembler::*avx_op)(XMMRegister, XMMRegister, XMMRegister),
2871 void (Assembler::*sse_op)(XMMRegister, XMMRegister), uint8_t width>
2872void EmitSimdShiftOp(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
2873 LiftoffRegister operand, LiftoffRegister count) {
2874 static constexpr RegClass tmp_rc = reg_class_for(kI32);
2875 LiftoffRegister tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(tmp_rc, LiftoffRegList{count});
2876 constexpr int mask = (1 << width) - 1;
2877
2878 assm->mov(tmp.gp(), count.gp());
2879 assm->and_(tmp.gp(), Immediate(mask));
2880 assm->Movd(kScratchDoubleReg, tmp.gp());
2881 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
2882 CpuFeatureScope scope(assm, AVX);
2883 (assm->*avx_op)(dst.fp(), operand.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
2884 } else {
2885 if (dst.fp() != operand.fp()) assm->movaps(dst.fp(), operand.fp());
2886 (assm->*sse_op)(dst.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
2887 }
2888}
2889
2890template <void (Assembler::*avx_op)(XMMRegister, XMMRegister, uint8_t),
2891 void (Assembler::*sse_op)(XMMRegister, uint8_t), uint8_t width>
2892void EmitSimdShiftOpImm(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
2893 LiftoffRegister operand, int32_t count) {
2894 constexpr int mask = (1 << width) - 1;
2895 uint8_t shift = static_cast<uint8_t>(count & mask);
2896 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
2897 CpuFeatureScope scope(assm, AVX);
2898 (assm->*avx_op)(dst.fp(), operand.fp(), shift);
2899 } else {
2900 if (dst.fp() != operand.fp()) assm->movaps(dst.fp(), operand.fp());
2901 (assm->*sse_op)(dst.fp(), shift);
2902 }
2903}

2905inline void EmitAnyTrue(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
2906 LiftoffRegister src) {
2907 Register tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, LiftoffRegList{dst}).gp();
2908 assm->xor_(tmp, tmp);
2909 assm->mov(dst.gp(), Immediate(1));
2910 assm->Ptest(src.fp(), src.fp());
2911 assm->cmov(zero, dst.gp(), tmp);
2912}

2914template <void (SharedMacroAssemblerBase::*pcmp)(XMMRegister, XMMRegister)>
2915inline void EmitAllTrue(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
2916 LiftoffRegister src,
2917 std::optional<CpuFeature> feature = std::nullopt) {
2918 std::optional<CpuFeatureScope> sse_scope;
2919 if (feature.has_value()) sse_scope.emplace(assm, *feature);
2920
2921 Register tmp = assm->GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, LiftoffRegList{dst}).gp();
2922 XMMRegister tmp_simd = liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg;
2923 assm->mov(tmp, Immediate(1));
2924 assm->xor_(dst.gp(), dst.gp());
2925 assm->Pxor(tmp_simd, tmp_simd);
2926 (assm->*pcmp)(tmp_simd, src.fp());
2927 assm->Ptest(tmp_simd, tmp_simd);
2928 assm->cmov(zero, dst.gp(), tmp);
2929}

2933void LiftoffAssembler::LoadTransform(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
2934 Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
2935 LoadType type,
2936 LoadTransformationKind transform,
2937 uint32_t* protected_load_pc) {
2938 DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
2939 Operand src_op{src_addr, offset_reg, times_1,
2940 static_cast<int32_t>(offset_imm)};
2941 *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
2942
2943 MachineType memtype = type.mem_type();
2944 if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kExtend) {
2945 if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
2946 Pmovsxbw(dst.fp(), src_op);
2947 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint8()) {
2948 Pmovzxbw(dst.fp(), src_op);
2949 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
2950 Pmovsxwd(dst.fp(), src_op);
2951 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint16()) {
2952 Pmovzxwd(dst.fp(), src_op);
2953 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2954 Pmovsxdq(dst.fp(), src_op);
2955 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint32()) {
2956 Pmovzxdq(dst.fp(), src_op);
2957 }
2958 } else if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kZeroExtend) {
2959 if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2960 Movss(dst.fp(), src_op);
2961 } else {
2962 DCHECK_EQ(MachineType::Int64(), memtype);
2963 Movsd(dst.fp(), src_op);
2964 }
2965 } else {
2966 DCHECK_EQ(LoadTransformationKind::kSplat, transform);
2967 if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
2968 S128Load8Splat(dst.fp(), src_op, liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
2969 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
2970 S128Load16Splat(dst.fp(), src_op, liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
2971 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2972 S128Load32Splat(dst.fp(), src_op);
2973 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int64()) {
2974 Movddup(dst.fp(), src_op);
2975 }
2976 }
2977}

2979void LiftoffAssembler::LoadLane(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src,
2980 Register addr, Register offset_reg,
2981 uintptr_t offset_imm, LoadType type,
2982 uint8_t laneidx, uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
2983 bool /* i64_offset */) {
2984 DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
2985 Operand src_op{addr, offset_reg, times_1, static_cast<int32_t>(offset_imm)};
2986 *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
2987
2988 MachineType mem_type = type.mem_type();
2989 if (mem_type == MachineType::Int8()) {
2990 Pinsrb(dst.fp(), src.fp(), src_op, laneidx);
2991 } else if (mem_type == MachineType::Int16()) {
2992 Pinsrw(dst.fp(), src.fp(), src_op, laneidx);
2993 } else if (mem_type == MachineType::Int32()) {
2994 Pinsrd(dst.fp(), src.fp(), src_op, laneidx);
2995 } else {
2996 DCHECK_EQ(MachineType::Int64(), mem_type);
2997 if (laneidx == 0) {
2998 Movlps(dst.fp(), src.fp(), src_op);
2999 } else {
3000 DCHECK_EQ(1, laneidx);
3001 Movhps(dst.fp(), src.fp(), src_op);
3002 }
3003 }
3004}

3006void LiftoffAssembler::StoreLane(Register dst, Register offset,
3007 uintptr_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
3008 StoreType type, uint8_t lane,
3009 uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
3010 bool /* i64_offset */) {
3011 DCHECK_LE(offset_imm, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
3012 Operand dst_op = Operand(dst, offset, times_1, offset_imm);
3013 if (protected_store_pc) *protected_store_pc = pc_offset();
3014
3015 MachineRepresentation rep = type.mem_rep();
3016 if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord8) {
3017 Pextrb(dst_op, src.fp(), lane);
3018 } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord16) {
3019 Pextrw(dst_op, src.fp(), lane);
3020 } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord32) {
3021 S128Store32Lane(dst_op, src.fp(), lane);
3022 } else {
3023 DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kWord64, rep);
3024 S128Store64Lane(dst_op, src.fp(), lane);
3025 }
3026}

3028void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_shuffle(LiftoffRegister dst,
3029 LiftoffRegister lhs,
3030 LiftoffRegister rhs,
3031 const uint8_t shuffle[16],
3032 bool is_swizzle) {
3033 LiftoffRegister tmp = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, {});
3034 // Prepare 16 byte aligned buffer for shuffle control mask.
3035 mov(tmp.gp(), esp);
3036 and_(esp, -16);
3037
3038 if (is_swizzle) {
3039 uint32_t imms[4];
3040 // Shuffles that use just 1 operand are called swizzles, rhs can be ignored.
3041 wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack16Lanes(imms, shuffle);
3042 for (int i = 3; i >= 0; i--) {
3043 push_imm32(imms[i]);
3044 }
3045 Pshufb(dst.fp(), lhs.fp(), Operand(esp, 0));
3046 mov(esp, tmp.gp());
3047 return;
3048 }
3049
3050 movups(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, lhs.fp());
3051 for (int i = 3; i >= 0; i--) {
3052 uint32_t mask = 0;
3053 for (int j = 3; j >= 0; j--) {
3054 uint8_t lane = shuffle[i * 4 + j];
3055 mask <<= 8;
3056 mask |= lane < kSimd128Size ? lane : 0x80;
3057 }
3058 push(Immediate(mask));
3059 }
3060 Pshufb(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, lhs.fp(), Operand(esp, 0));
3061
3062 for (int i = 3; i >= 0; i--) {
3063 uint32_t mask = 0;
3064 for (int j = 3; j >= 0; j--) {
3065 uint8_t lane = shuffle[i * 4 + j];
3066 mask <<= 8;
3067 mask |= lane >= kSimd128Size ? (lane & 0x0F) : 0x80;
3068 }
3069 push(Immediate(mask));
3070 }
3071 Pshufb(dst.fp(), rhs.fp(), Operand(esp, 0));
3072 Por(dst.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3073 mov(esp, tmp.gp());
3074}

3112void LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_relaxed_laneselect(LiftoffRegister dst,
3113 LiftoffRegister src1,
3114 LiftoffRegister src2,
3115 LiftoffRegister mask,
3116 int lane_width) {
3117 // Passing {src2} first is not a typo: the x86 instructions copy from the
3118 // second operand when the mask is 1, contrary to the Wasm instruction.
3119 if (lane_width == 8) {
3120 Pblendvb(dst.fp(), src2.fp(), src1.fp(), mask.fp());
3121 } else if (lane_width == 32) {
3122 Blendvps(dst.fp(), src2.fp(), src1.fp(), mask.fp());
3123 } else if (lane_width == 64) {
3124 Blendvpd(dst.fp(), src2.fp(), src1.fp(), mask.fp());
3125 } else {
3126 UNREACHABLE();
3127 }
3128}

3362void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64x2_gt_s(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
3363 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
3364 // Different register alias requirements depending on CpuFeatures supported:
3365 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX) || CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SSE4_2)) {
3366 // 1. AVX, or SSE4_2 no requirements (I64x2GtS takes care of aliasing).
3367 I64x2GtS(dst.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3368 } else {
3369 // 2. Else, dst != lhs && dst != rhs (lhs == rhs is ok).
3370 if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
3371 LiftoffRegister tmp =
3372 GetUnusedRegister(RegClass::kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{lhs, rhs});
3373 I64x2GtS(tmp.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3374 movaps(dst.fp(), tmp.fp());
3375 } else {
3376 I64x2GtS(dst.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3377 }
3378 }
3379}
3380
3381void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64x2_ge_s(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
3382 LiftoffRegister rhs) {
3383 // Different register alias requirements depending on CpuFeatures supported:
3384 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
3385 // 1. AVX, no requirements.
3386 I64x2GeS(dst.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3387 } else if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SSE4_2)) {
3388 // 2. SSE4_2, dst != lhs.
3389 if (dst == lhs) {
3390 LiftoffRegister tmp =
3391 GetUnusedRegister(RegClass::kFpReg, {rhs}, LiftoffRegList{lhs});
3392 // macro-assembler uses kScratchDoubleReg, so don't use it.
3393 I64x2GeS(tmp.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3394 movaps(dst.fp(), tmp.fp());
3395 } else {
3396 I64x2GeS(dst.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3397 }
3398 } else {
3399 // 3. Else, dst != lhs && dst != rhs (lhs == rhs is ok).
3400 if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
3401 LiftoffRegister tmp =
3402 GetUnusedRegister(RegClass::kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{lhs, rhs});
3403 I64x2GeS(tmp.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3404 movaps(dst.fp(), tmp.fp());
3405 } else {
3406 I64x2GeS(dst.fp(), lhs.fp(), rhs.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3407 }
3408 }
3409}
