3463void LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_const(LiftoffRegister dst,
3464 const uint8_t imms[16]) {
3465 uint64_t vals[2];
3466 memcpy(vals, imms, sizeof(vals));
3467 MacroAssembler::Move(dst.fp(), vals[0]);
3468
3469 uint64_t high = vals[1];
3470 Register tmp = GetUnusedRegister(RegClass::kGpReg, {}).gp();
3471 MacroAssembler::Move(tmp, Immediate(high & 0xffff'ffff));
3472 Pinsrd(dst.fp(), tmp, 2);
3473
3474 MacroAssembler::Move(tmp, Immediate(high >> 32));
3475 Pinsrd(dst.fp(), tmp, 3);
3476}

3500void LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_select(LiftoffRegister dst,
3501 LiftoffRegister src1,
3502 LiftoffRegister src2,
3503 LiftoffRegister mask) {
3504 // Ensure that we don't overwrite any inputs with the movaps below.
3505 DCHECK_NE(dst, src1);
3506 DCHECK_NE(dst, src2);
3507 if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX) && dst != mask) {
3508 movaps(dst.fp(), mask.fp());
3509 S128Select(dst.fp(), dst.fp(), src1.fp(), src2.fp(),
3510 liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3511 } else {
3512 S128Select(dst.fp(), mask.fp(), src1.fp(), src2.fp(),
3513 liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
3514 }
3515}

3991
3992namespace liftoff {
3993// Helper function to check for register aliasing, AVX support, and moves
3994// registers around before calling the actual macro-assembler function.
3995inline void I32x4ExtMulHelper(LiftoffAssembler* assm, XMMRegister dst,
3996 XMMRegister src1, XMMRegister src2, bool low,
3997 bool is_signed) {
3998 // I32x4ExtMul requires dst == src1 if AVX is not supported.
3999 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX) || dst == src1) {
4000 assm->I32x4ExtMul(dst, src1, src2, liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, low,
4001 is_signed);
4002 } else if (dst != src2) {
4003 // dst != src1 && dst != src2
4004 assm->movaps(dst, src1);
4005 assm->I32x4ExtMul(dst, dst, src2, liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, low,
4006 is_signed);
4007 } else {
4008 // dst == src2
4009 // Extended multiplication is commutative,
4010 assm->movaps(dst, src2);
4011 assm->I32x4ExtMul(dst, dst, src1, liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, low,
4012 is_signed);
4013 }
4014}
4015} // namespace liftoff

4424void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32x4_uconvert_i32x4(LiftoffRegister dst,
4425 LiftoffRegister src) {
4426 Pxor(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg); // Zeros.
4427 Pblendw(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp(),
4428 uint8_t{0x55}); // Get lo 16 bits.
4429 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
4430 CpuFeatureScope scope(this, AVX);
4431 vpsubd(dst.fp(), src.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg); // Get hi 16 bits.
4432 } else {
4433 if (dst.fp() != src.fp()) movaps(dst.fp(), src.fp());
4434 psubd(dst.fp(), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
4435 }
4436 Cvtdq2ps(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg,
4437 liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg); // Convert lo exactly.
4438 Psrld(dst.fp(), dst.fp(), uint8_t{1}); // Div by 2 to get in unsigned range.
4439 Cvtdq2ps(dst.fp(), dst.fp()); // Convert hi, exactly.
4440 Addps(dst.fp(), dst.fp(), dst.fp()); // Double hi, exactly.
4441 Addps(dst.fp(), dst.fp(),
4442 liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg); // Add hi and lo, may round.
4443}

4447 Cvtpd2ps(dst.fp(), src.fp());
4448}

4901void LiftoffAssembler::StackCheck(Label* ool_code) {
4902 CompareStackLimit(esp, StackLimitKind::kInterruptStackLimit);
4903 j(below_equal, ool_code);
4904}

4909
4910void LiftoffAssembler::PushRegisters(LiftoffRegList regs) {
4911 LiftoffRegList gp_regs = regs & kGpCacheRegList;
4912 while (!gp_regs.is_empty()) {
4913 LiftoffRegister reg = gp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
4914 push(reg.gp());
4915 gp_regs.clear(reg);
4916 }
4917 LiftoffRegList fp_regs = regs & kFpCacheRegList;
4918 unsigned num_fp_regs = fp_regs.GetNumRegsSet();
4919 if (num_fp_regs) {
4920 AllocateStackSpace(num_fp_regs * kSimd128Size);
4921 unsigned offset = 0;
4922 while (!fp_regs.is_empty()) {
4923 LiftoffRegister reg = fp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
4924 Movdqu(Operand(esp, offset), reg.fp());
4925 fp_regs.clear(reg);
4926 offset += kSimd128Size;
4927 }
4928 DCHECK_EQ(offset, num_fp_regs * kSimd128Size);
4929 }
4930}
4931
4932void LiftoffAssembler::PopRegisters(LiftoffRegList regs) {
4933 LiftoffRegList fp_regs = regs & kFpCacheRegList;
4934 unsigned fp_offset = 0;
4935 while (!fp_regs.is_empty()) {
4936 LiftoffRegister reg = fp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
4937 Movdqu(reg.fp(), Operand(esp, fp_offset));
4938 fp_regs.clear(reg);
4939 fp_offset += kSimd128Size;
4940 }
4941 if (fp_offset) add(esp, Immediate(fp_offset));
4942 LiftoffRegList gp_regs = regs & kGpCacheRegList;
4943 while (!gp_regs.is_empty()) {
4944 LiftoffRegister reg = gp_regs.GetLastRegSet();
4945 pop(reg.gp());
4946 gp_regs.clear(reg);
4947 }
4948}
4949
4950void LiftoffAssembler::RecordSpillsInSafepoint(
4951 SafepointTableBuilder::Safepoint& safepoint, LiftoffRegList all_spills,
4952 LiftoffRegList ref_spills, int spill_offset) {
4953 LiftoffRegList fp_spills = all_spills & kFpCacheRegList;
4954 int spill_space_size = fp_spills.GetNumRegsSet() * kSimd128Size;
4955 LiftoffRegList gp_spills = all_spills & kGpCacheRegList;
4956 while (!gp_spills.is_empty()) {
4957 LiftoffRegister reg = gp_spills.GetFirstRegSet();
4958 if (ref_spills.has(reg)) {
4959 safepoint.DefineTaggedStackSlot(spill_offset);
4960 }
4961 gp_spills.clear(reg);
4962 ++spill_offset;
4963 spill_space_size += kSystemPointerSize;
4964 }
4965 // Record the number of additional spill slots.
4966 RecordOolSpillSpaceSize(spill_space_size);
4967}
4968
4969void LiftoffAssembler::DropStackSlotsAndRet(uint32_t num_stack_slots) {
4970 DCHECK_LT(num_stack_slots,
4971 (1 << 16) / kSystemPointerSize); // 16 bit immediate
4972 ret(static_cast<int>(num_stack_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
4973}
4974
4975void LiftoffAssembler::CallCWithStackBuffer(
4976 const std::initializer_list<VarState> args, const LiftoffRegister* rets,
4977 ValueKind return_kind, ValueKind out_argument_kind, int stack_bytes,
4978 ExternalReference ext_ref) {
4979 AllocateStackSpace(stack_bytes);
4980
4981 int arg_offset = 0;
4982 for (const VarState& arg : args) {
4983 if (arg.is_reg()) {
4984 liftoff::Store(this, esp, arg_offset, arg.reg(), arg.kind());
4985 } else if (arg.is_const()) {
4986 DCHECK_EQ(kI32, arg.kind());
4987 mov(Operand(esp, arg_offset), Immediate(arg.i32_const()));
4988 } else if (value_kind_size(arg.kind()) == 4) {
4989 // We do not have a scratch register, so move via the stack. Note that
4990 // {push} decrements {esp} by 4 and {pop} increments it again, but the
4991 // destionation operand uses the {esp} value after increasing.
4992 push(liftoff::GetStackSlot(arg.offset()));
4993 pop(Operand(esp, arg_offset));
4994 } else {
4995 DCHECK_EQ(8, value_kind_size(arg.kind()));
4996 push(liftoff::GetStackSlot(arg.offset()));
4997 pop(Operand(esp, arg_offset + 4));
4998 push(liftoff::GetStackSlot(arg.offset() + 4));
4999 pop(Operand(esp, arg_offset));
5000 }
5001 arg_offset += value_kind_size(arg.kind());
5002 }
5003 DCHECK_LE(arg_offset, stack_bytes);
5004
5005 constexpr Register kScratch = eax;
5006 constexpr Register kArgumentBuffer = ecx;
5007 constexpr int kNumCCallArgs = 1;
5008 mov(kArgumentBuffer, esp);
5009 PrepareCallCFunction(kNumCCallArgs, kScratch);
5010
5011 // Pass a pointer to the buffer with the arguments to the C function. ia32
5012 // does not use registers here, so push to the stack.
5013 mov(Operand(esp, 0), kArgumentBuffer);
5014
5015 // Now call the C function.
5016 CallCFunction(ext_ref, kNumCCallArgs);
5017
5018 // Move return value to the right register.
5019 const LiftoffRegister* next_result_reg = rets;
5020 if (return_kind != kVoid) {
5021 constexpr Register kReturnReg = eax;
5022 if (kReturnReg != next_result_reg->gp()) {
5023 Move(*next_result_reg, LiftoffRegister(kReturnReg), return_kind);
5024 }
5025 ++next_result_reg;
5026 }
5027
5028 // Load potential output value from the buffer on the stack.
5029 if (out_argument_kind != kVoid) {
5030 liftoff::Load(this, *next_result_reg, esp, 0, out_argument_kind);
5031 }
5032
5033 add(esp, Immediate(stack_bytes));
5034}
5035
5036void LiftoffAssembler::CallC(const std::initializer_list<VarState> args,
5037 ExternalReference ext_ref) {
5038 LiftoffRegList arg_regs;
5039 for (const VarState arg : args) {
5040 if (arg.is_reg()) arg_regs.set(arg.reg());
5041 }
5042
5043 RegList usable_regs = kLiftoffAssemblerGpCacheRegs - arg_regs.GetGpList();
5044 Register scratch = usable_regs.first();
5045 int num_lowered_args = 0;
5046 // i64 arguments are lowered to two actual arguments (taking two stack slots).
5047 for (const VarState& arg : args) {
5048 num_lowered_args += arg.kind() == kI64 ? 2 : 1;
5049 }
5050 PrepareCallCFunction(num_lowered_args, scratch);
5051
5052 // Ia32 passes all arguments via the stack. Store them now in the stack space
5053 // allocated by {PrepareCallCFunction}.
5054
5055 // GetNextOperand returns the operand for the next stack slot on each
5056 // invocation.
5057 auto GetNextOperand = [arg_offset = 0, num_lowered_args]() mutable {
5058 // Check that we don't exceed the pre-computed {num_stack_slots}.
5059 DCHECK_GE(num_lowered_args, arg_offset);
5060 USE(num_lowered_args);
5061 return Operand{esp, arg_offset++ * kSystemPointerSize};
5062 };
5063 for (const VarState& arg : args) {
5064 Operand dst = GetNextOperand();
5065 if (arg.is_reg()) {
5066 LiftoffRegister reg = arg.reg();
5067 if (arg.kind() == kI64) {
5068 mov(dst, reg.low_gp());
5069 mov(GetNextOperand(), reg.high_gp());
5070 } else {
5071 mov(dst, reg.gp());
5072 }
5073 } else if (arg.is_const()) {
5074 DCHECK_EQ(kI32, arg.kind());
5075 mov(dst, Immediate(arg.i32_const()));
5076 } else {
5077 DCHECK(arg.is_stack());
5078 if (arg.kind() == kI64) {
5079 mov(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(arg.offset()));
5080 mov(dst, scratch);
5081 mov(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(arg.offset() + kSystemPointerSize));
5082 mov(GetNextOperand(), scratch);
5083 } else {
5084 mov(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(arg.offset()));
5085 mov(dst, scratch);
5086 }
5087 }
5088 }
5089
5090 // Now call the C function.
5091 CallCFunction(ext_ref, num_lowered_args);
5092}

5172void LiftoffStackSlots::Construct(int param_slots) {
5173 DCHECK_LT(0, slots_.size());
5174 SortInPushOrder();
5175 int last_stack_slot = param_slots;
5176 for (auto& slot : slots_) {
5177 const int stack_slot = slot.dst_slot_;
5178 int stack_decrement = (last_stack_slot - stack_slot) * kSystemPointerSize;
5179 DCHECK_LT(0, stack_decrement);
5180 last_stack_slot = stack_slot;
5181 const LiftoffAssembler::VarState& src = slot.src_;
5182 switch (src.loc()) {
5183 case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kStack:
5184 // The combination of AllocateStackSpace and 2 movdqu is usually smaller
5185 // in code size than doing 4 pushes.
5186 if (src.kind() == kS128) {
5187 asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement);
5188 asm_->movdqu(liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg,
5189 liftoff::GetStackSlot(slot.src_offset_));
5190 asm_->movdqu(Operand(esp, 0), liftoff::kScratchDoubleReg);
5191 break;
5192 }
5193 if (src.kind() == kF64) {
5194 asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kDoubleSize);
5195 DCHECK_EQ(kLowWord, slot.half_);
5196 asm_->push(liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(slot.src_offset_, kHighWord));
5197 stack_decrement = kSystemPointerSize;
5198 }
5199 asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kSystemPointerSize);
5200 asm_->push(liftoff::GetHalfStackSlot(slot.src_offset_, slot.half_));
5201 break;
5202 case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kRegister:
5203 if (src.kind() == kI64) {
5204 liftoff::push(
5205 asm_, slot.half_ == kLowWord ? src.reg().low() : src.reg().high(),
5206 kI32, stack_decrement - kSystemPointerSize);
5207 } else {
5208 int pushed_bytes = SlotSizeInBytes(slot);
5209 liftoff::push(asm_, src.reg(), src.kind(),
5210 stack_decrement - pushed_bytes);
5211 }
5212 break;
5213 case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kIntConst:
5214 asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kSystemPointerSize);
5215 // The high word is the sign extension of the low word.
5216 asm_->push(Immediate(slot.half_ == kLowWord ? src.i32_const()
5217 : src.i32_const() >> 31));
5218 break;
5219 }
5220 }
5221}
